# Database Conventions

## Migrations

- All migrations are Liquibase SQL files in `src/main/resources/com/orinuno/db/changelog/scripts/`
- File naming: `YYYYMMDDHHMMSS_description.sql`
- Each file starts with `--liquibase formatted sql` and `--changeset orinuno:YYYYMMDDHHMMSS`
- Register every new migration in `liquibase-changelog.yaml`
- Engine: InnoDB, charset: utf8mb4, collation: utf8mb4_unicode_ci

## MyBatis

- Mapper interfaces in `com.orinuno.repository` with `@Mapper` annotation
- XML mappers in `src/main/resources/com/orinuno/db/mapper/`
- Always define `resultMap` — do not rely on auto-mapping
- Use `#{param}` for parameterized values, `${param}` only for pre-validated sort/order fields

## Critical Rules

- **COALESCE upsert**: When upserting `kodik_episode_variant`, use `COALESCE(VALUES(mp4_link), mp4_link)` to preserve existing decoded links
- **TTL tracking**: `updateMp4Link` must always set `mp4_link_decoded_at = NOW()`
- Table `kodik_episode_variant` has a composite unique key `(content_id, season_number, episode_number, translation_id)` — use `ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE` for upserts
